# c1
> (openai + claude).best
< cost <= $3.33
< latency <= 3m
@forward c2
@text <500

Find a realistic HFT hypothesis for Binance USDM.
Account for fees, latency, fill probability, adverse selection, and overfit risk.
Return a compact hypothesis with the market condition, expected edge, and failure modes.

# c2
> openrouter:openrouter/auto
@forward c3
@text <700

Critically review the candidate from %from c1.
Keep the idea only if it can survive live fees, real queue priority, and stale-book risk.
Return:
hypothesis =
reason =
blocking_risks =

# c3
> claude.max
@file -markdown hypothesis_report.md

Package the reviewed idea from %from c2 as a short research memo.
Include assumptions, measurements needed, rejection criteria, and the next experiment.
